# AAEC — AI Autonomous Email Copilot
# Complete Implementation Plan (10 Phases)

> **Stack:** Node.js + Express | Supabase | Gemini 1.5 Flash | Telegram Bot | Gmail API | Google Apps Script
> **Target:** < 10MB project size | 100% free-tier infrastructure | Single-user first, multi-user ready

---

## Phase 1 — Project Foundation & Database Setup

### 1.1 Project Structure

```
E-Mail AI Agent/
├── src/
│   ├── server.js                  # Express app entry point
│   ├── config/
│   │   ├── env.js                 # Environment variable loader + validation
│   │   ├── constants.js           # App-wide constants (timeouts, limits, keywords)
│   │   └── supabase.js            # Supabase client initialization
│   ├── agents/
│   │   ├── intake.js              # Agent 1 — Intake Agent
│   │   ├── filter.js              # Agent 2 — Filter Agent
│   │   ├── contextBuilder.js      # Agent 3 — Context Builder Agent
│   │   ├── aiBrain.js             # Agent 4 — AI Brain Agent
│   │   ├── autonomy.js            # Agent 5 — Autonomy Agent
│   │   ├── vault.js               # Agent 6 — Document Vault Agent
│   │   ├── notification.js        # Agent 7 — Notification Agent
│   │   ├── send.js                # Agent 8 — Send Agent
│   │   ├── memory.js              # Agent 9 — Memory Agent
│   │   └── mentor.js              # Agent 10 — Mentor Agent
│   ├── services/
│   │   ├── gmail.js               # Gmail API wrapper (read, send, labels, threads)
│   │   ├── calendar.js            # Google Calendar API wrapper
│   │   ├── ai.js                  # AI provider abstraction (Gemini → DeepSeek → OpenAI)
│   │   ├── telegram.js            # Telegram Bot API wrapper + command router
│   │   └── encryption.js          # AES-256 encrypt/decrypt for tokens & keys
│   ├── routes/
│   │   ├── webhook.js             # POST /webhook/email — Apps Script trigger endpoint
│   │   ├── telegram.js            # POST /webhook/telegram — Telegram updates
│   │   ├── oauth.js               # GET /auth/google/callback — OAuth2 flow
│   │   └── health.js              # GET /health — keep-alive + status
│   ├── middleware/
│   │   ├── auth.js                # Webhook signature verification
│   │   ├── rateLimiter.js         # Express rate limiter
│   │   └── errorHandler.js        # Global error handler
│   ├── utils/
│   │   ├── queue.js               # In-memory queue with Supabase persistence fallback
│   │   ├── logger.js              # Structured logging (console, no external deps)
│   │   ├── helpers.js             # Date, string, timezone utilities
│   │   └── mime.js                # MIME message builder for Gmail send
│   └── templates/
│       └── telegramMessages.js    # All Telegram message templates (formatted)
├── scripts/
│   ├── appsScript.js              # Google Apps Script code (copy to GAS editor)
│   └── setup.js                   # One-time setup script (DB tables, bot commands)
├── .env.example                   # Template for environment variables
├── .gitignore
├── package.json
├── README.md
└── skill.md                       # Original system design document
```

**Total files: ~30 | Estimated size: < 500KB code + deps under 10MB**

### 1.2 Package Dependencies (Minimal)

```json
{
  "dependencies": {
    "express": "^4.18.2",
    "@supabase/supabase-js": "^2.39.0",
    "googleapis": "^130.0.0",
    "@google/generative-ai": "^0.21.0",
    "node-telegram-bot-api": "^0.66.0",
    "dotenv": "^16.3.1",
    "uuid": "^9.0.0",
    "sharp": "^0.33.0",
    "express-rate-limit": "^7.1.4"
  }
}
```

> **Size note:** `googleapis` is heavy (~40MB). We'll use **selective imports** (`googleapis/build/src/apis/gmail`, `googleapis/build/src/apis/calendar`) to keep `node_modules` lean. Alternative: use raw `fetch()` calls to Google APIs to eliminate this dependency entirely (reduces to ~5MB total).

### 1.3 Express Server Setup — `src/server.js`

| Feature | Detail |
|---|---|
| Port | `process.env.PORT \|\| 3000` |
| JSON body parser | `express.json({ limit: '5mb' })` for file uploads |
| CORS | Disabled (API-only, no browser clients) |
| Routes mounted | `/webhook/email`, `/webhook/telegram`, `/auth/google/*`, `/health` |
| Error handler | Global middleware catches all unhandled errors, logs + notifies via Telegram |
| Startup | Connect Supabase, set Telegram webhook, start cron intervals, log ready |

### 1.4 Environment Configuration — `src/config/env.js`

Validates ALL required env vars on startup. Throws clear error if any missing:

```
PORT, NODE_ENV
SUPABASE_URL, SUPABASE_SERVICE_KEY
GEMINI_API_KEY
DEEPSEEK_API_KEY (optional)
OPENAI_API_KEY (optional)
GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID, GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET, GOOGLE_REDIRECT_URI
TELEGRAM_BOT_TOKEN
ENCRYPTION_KEY (32-byte hex for AES-256)
SYSTEM_ALERT_TELEGRAM_ID
USER_TIMEZONE (default: Asia/Kolkata)
```

### 1.5 Supabase Database Schema — 10 Tables

All tables created via `scripts/setup.js` or Supabase dashboard migration.

**Table 1 — `users`** (multi-user ready)
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| id | UUID PK | `gen_random_uuid()` |
| email | TEXT UNIQUE | Gmail address |
| telegram_chat_id | TEXT UNIQUE | Telegram user ID |
| gmail_token | JSONB | Encrypted OAuth2 tokens (access + refresh) |
| calendar_enabled | BOOLEAN | Default `true` |
| gemini_key_encrypted | TEXT | BYOK — user's own Gemini key |
| plan | TEXT | `free` / `pro` |
| created_at | TIMESTAMPTZ | `NOW()` |

**Table 2 — `memory`** (Agent 9 — core user profile)
| Column | Type | Notes |
|---|---|---|
| user_id | UUID PK FK→users | One per user |
| tone_style | TEXT | `formal` / `casual` / `friendly` |
| formality_score | INTEGER | 0–100 |
| avg_reply_length | TEXT | `short` / `medium` / `detailed` |
| common_phrases | JSONB | `["Hi X,", "Thanks,"]` |
| phrase_bank | JSONB | Frequently used phrases |
| writing_quirks | JSONB | Unique patterns |
| sign_off | TEXT | e.g. "Thanks, Arjun" |
| language | TEXT | `en`, `ta`, `hi` |
| timezone | TEXT | `Asia/Kolkata` |
| sleep_start / sleep_end | INTEGER | 22, 7 |
| response_speed | TEXT | `fast` / `moderate` / `slow` |
| edit_patterns | JSONB | AI draft vs user edits |
| accuracy_score | INTEGER | Tracks draft acceptance rate |
| updated_at | TIMESTAMPTZ | Auto-updated |

**Table 3 — `contact_memory`** (Agent 9 — per-contact)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| user_id + contact_email | Composite PK |
| contact_name | TEXT |
| relationship | TEXT (`client`/`colleague`/`vendor`/`personal`) |
| history_note | TEXT |
| preferred_tone | TEXT |
| is_vip / is_ignored | BOOLEAN |
| last_contact | TIMESTAMPTZ |
| email_count | INTEGER |

**Table 4 — `processed_emails`** (Agent 1 — idempotency)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| message_id | TEXT PK |
| user_id | UUID FK |
| status | TEXT (`processing`/`done`/`failed`) |
| locked_at / completed_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |

**Table 5 — `email_history`** (Agent 8 — sent log)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| id | UUID PK |
| user_id, message_id, thread_id, recipient, subject | TEXT |
| ai_draft, final_sent | TEXT |
| was_edited | BOOLEAN |
| edit_diff | JSONB |
| autonomy_level, confidence | INTEGER |
| sent_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |

**Table 6 — `vault_metadata`** (Agent 6 — document index)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| id | UUID PK |
| user_id | UUID FK |
| file_path, file_hash, original_filename, file_type | TEXT |
| size_kb | INTEGER |
| doc_type | TEXT (`receipt`/`ticket`/`invoice`/`contract`/`other`) |
| vendor, amount, summary | TEXT |
| doc_date, expiry_date | DATE |
| importance | TEXT (`permanent`/`90days`/`30days`) |
| search_tags | TEXT[] |
| extracted_text | TEXT |
| source | TEXT (`email`/`telegram`) |
| email_sender | TEXT |
| expires_at, created_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |

**Table 7 — `pending_sends`** (Agent 5 — survives restarts)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| id | UUID PK |
| user_id | UUID FK |
| email_to, subject, body | TEXT |
| attachments | JSONB |
| thread_id, telegram_message_id | TEXT |
| send_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |
| status | TEXT (`pending`/`sent`/`cancelled`) |
| created_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |

**Table 8 — `follow_ups`** (Agent 10 — tracking)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| id | UUID PK |
| user_id | UUID FK |
| message_id, recipient, subject | TEXT |
| sent_at, follow_up_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |
| status | TEXT (`pending`/`sent`/`dismissed`) |
| reminder_sent | BOOLEAN |

**Table 9 — `user_status`** (away/active)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| user_id | UUID PK FK |
| status | TEXT (`active`/`away`/`paused`) |
| away_until | TIMESTAMPTZ |
| updated_at | TIMESTAMPTZ |

**Table 10 — `auto_send_whitelist`** (user-controlled auto-send)
| Column | Type |
|---|---|
| user_id + email_intent | Composite PK |
| enabled | BOOLEAN |
| delay_mins | INTEGER (default 3) |
| undo_mins | INTEGER (default 15) |

**Supabase Storage:** One bucket `vault` for document files.

