## Phase 4 — Agent 5 (Autonomy) + Agent 7 (Notification)

### 4.1 Agent 5: Autonomy — `src/agents/autonomy.js`

**Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `decide(aiResult, userSettings, isHardStop)` | Returns `{ level, reason, delay_mins, undo_mins }` |
| `handleLevel1(userId, aiResult)` | Draft ready → send to Notification Agent for Telegram display |
| `handleLevel2(userId, aiResult)` | Whitelisted → persist to `pending_sends` → delayed send with undo |
| `handleLevel3(userId, aiResult)` | Hard stop → send to Notification with full context, must approve |
| `handleTimeout(userId, emailId, priority)` | Timeout logic based on priority tier (routine/important/urgent/VIP/night) |
| `checkPendingSends()` | Interval (60s) → query `pending_sends` where `send_at <= now` → send |

**Decision matrix:**
1. Hard stop OR `aiResult.hard_stop` → Level 3 (always)
2. `intent === 'meeting_request'` → Level 3 (always)
3. `confidence < 75` → Level 3
4. Whitelisted category AND `confidence >= 90` → Level 2 (3 min delay, 15 min undo)
5. Default → Level 1 (draft + notify)

**Timeout rules (from constants):**
| Priority | Wait | After Timeout | Reminders |
|---|---|---|---|
| Routine (<50) | 30 min | Add to digest | 0 |
| Important (50-79) | 2 hours | Remind once | 1 |
| Urgent (80+) | 15 min | Remind | 2 (every 30 min) |
| VIP | 10 min | Remind | 3 (every 20 min) |
| Night (10pm-7am) | Until 7am | Morning digest | 0 |

### 4.2 Telegram Service — `src/services/telegram.js`

**Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `initialize()` | Set webhook URL, register bot commands |
| `sendMessage(chatId, text, options)` | Send formatted message with inline keyboard |
| `sendWithButtons(chatId, text, buttons)` | Send message with action buttons |
| `editMessage(chatId, messageId, text, buttons)` | Edit existing message (for undo countdown) |
| `handleCallback(callbackQuery)` | Process button clicks (Send/Edit/Reject/Undo/etc.) |
| `setWebhook(url)` | Register Telegram webhook URL |

### 4.3 Agent 7: Notification — `src/agents/notification.js`

**Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `notifyLevel1(userId, aiResult)` | Draft ready template + [Send][Edit][Later][Skip] buttons |
| `notifyLevel2Sent(userId, sendRecord)` | Auto-sent notification + [Undo (Xm left)][Thread] buttons |
| `notifyLevel3(userId, aiResult)` | Urgent template + [Send][Edit][Reject][Thread] buttons |
| `sendMorningDigest(userId)` | 7am digest: overnight count + urgent/important list |
| `sendEveningPromoDigest(userId)` | 6pm digest: curated promos (score 60+) |
| `sendWeeklyReport(userId, stats)` | Monday 9am: stats + suggestions + awaiting replies |
| `sendSystemHealth(userId, health)` | 8am: API usage, vault size, DB size, uptime |
| `sendSpamRescue(userId, email)` | Rescued from spam notification + [Move to inbox][VIP][Leave] |
| `sendDocumentStored(userId, analysis)` | Document stored notification + [View][Forward] |
| `canSend(userId)` | Rate limiter — max 1 message/second |

**Templates in `src/templates/telegramMessages.js`:**
All 10 message templates from skill.md Section 8, using Telegram MarkdownV2 formatting.

