## Phase 5 — Agent 8 (Send Agent)

### 5.1 MIME Builder — `src/utils/mime.js`

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `buildMimeMessage({ to, subject, body, threadId, attachments })` | Constructs RFC 2822 MIME message with proper `In-Reply-To` header for threading |
| `base64UrlEncode(buffer)` | Gmail API requires URL-safe base64 |
| `attachFile(mimeBuilder, fileBuffer, filename, mimeType)` | Adds multipart attachment |

### 5.2 Agent 8: Send — `src/agents/send.js`

**Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `sendEmail(draftId, userId)` | Main — safety check → attach vault doc → human delay → Gmail send → record history → start undo |
| `addHumanDelay()` | Random 90–180 second delay (looks natural) |
| `recordInHistory(userId, sendData)` | INSERT into `email_history` |
| `startUndoWindow(userId, messageId, undoMins)` | Stores undo expiry in memory + Supabase |
| `undoSend(userId, messageId)` | Check window → `gmail.trashMessage()` → notify user |
| `processPendingSend(sendRecord)` | Called by Autonomy Agent interval → execute queued send |

**Safety checks before every send:**
1. `hard_stop === true` → throw error
2. Undo window stored in Supabase → survives restart
3. History recorded with both `ai_draft` and `final_sent` for learning

