## Phase 7 — Agent 9 (Memory)

### 7.1 Agent 9: Memory — `src/agents/memory.js`

**Functions:**

| Function | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `bootstrap(userId)` | Day 1: Read last 50 sent emails → Gemini analyzes writing style → store profile |
| `getCoreMemory(userId)` | Returns Tier 1 constant memory (name, role, tone, sign-off) |
| `getContactMemory(userId, email)` | Returns Tier 2 for known sender (relationship, history, tone) |
| `getTopicMemory(userId, intent)` | Returns Tier 3 for matched intent |
| `learnFromInteraction(userId, interaction)` | Switch on type: edited/approved/rejected/vip/ignore |
| `handleDraftEdited(userId, aiDraft, finalSent)` | Compute diff → store pattern → adjust tone score |
| `handleDraftApproved(userId, draft)` | Reinforce style → increment accuracy |
| `handleDraftRejected(userId, draft, reason)` | Record what went wrong |
| `addVIP(userId, email)` | Set `is_vip=true` in `contact_memory` |
| `addIgnored(userId, email)` | Set `is_ignored=true` in `contact_memory` |
| `updateContactMemory(userId, senderEmail, data)` | Upsert contact relationship info |
| `detectToneDrift(userId)` | Weekly: compare recent 20 sent emails vs stored profile |

**Bootstrap process (first-time setup):**
1. Fetch 50 sent emails via Gmail API
2. Send to Gemini: "Analyze writing style" → extract tone, phrases, quirks, sign-off
3. 5 onboarding questions via Telegram (sign-off, tone, length, role, VIP senders)
4. Store combined profile in `memory` table

