## Phase 10 — System Health, Failsafes & Deployment

### 10.1 System Health — `src/middleware/errorHandler.js` + `src/utils/logger.js`

| Feature | Implementation |
|---|---|
| Global error handler | Express middleware catches unhandled errors → logs → sends Telegram alert |
| RAM monitor | Every 5 min: check `process.memoryUsage()` → warn at 70%, restart at 85% |
| Storage monitor | Daily: check Supabase DB size → warn at 70%, auto-cleanup at 80% |
| API usage tracking | Before every Gemini call → increment counter → warn at 80%, switch fallback at 97% |
| Structured logging | `src/utils/logger.js` — JSON logs with timestamp, level, agent, action |

### 10.2 Auto Cleanup — in `src/agents/mentor.js`

- Delete `processed_emails` locks older than 30 days (status `done`)
- Delete expired vault files (metadata kept forever for searchability)
- Supabase keep-alive ping every 3 days

### 10.3 Deployment — Render.com

| Config | Value |
|---|---|
| Service type | Web Service |
| Build command | `npm install` |
| Start command | `node src/server.js` |
| Instance | Free tier (spins down after 15m inactivity) |
| Keep-alive | cron-job.org pings `GET /health` every 10 min |
| Environment | All env vars set in Render dashboard |

### 10.4 Google Apps Script Deployment

1. Create new GAS project at script.google.com
2. Copy `scripts/appsScript.js` content
3. Set `RENDER_URL` and `WEBHOOK_SECRET` in GAS Script Properties
4. Create installable trigger: Gmail → new message → `onEmailReceived`

### 10.5 Supabase Storage Config

- Create `vault` bucket (private, 50MB max per file)
- RLS policies: users can only access their own files

---

## Complete Pipeline Flow

```
Gmail → Apps Script trigger
         ↓
    POST /webhook/email
         ↓
  Agent 1 (Intake) — dedup check → queue
         ↓
  Agent 2 (Filter) — classify bucket + hard stop check
         ↓
    ┌─ Bucket A → Agent 7 (Notify immediately)
    ├─ Bucket B → Store for digest
    ├─ Bucket C → Silent trash
    └─ Bucket D (NEEDS_AI) ↓
         ↓
  Agent 3 (Context) — thread + memory + calendar + vault
         ↓
  Agent 4 (AI Brain) — Gemini call → structured JSON
         ↓
  Agent 5 (Autonomy) — decide Level 1/2/3
         ↓
    ┌─ Level 1 → Agent 7 (Telegram draft + buttons)
    ├─ Level 2 → pending_sends → delayed auto-send
    └─ Level 3 → Agent 7 (urgent notification + must approve)
         ↓
  User taps button on Telegram
         ↓
    ┌─ [Send] → Agent 8 (human delay → Gmail send → history)
    ├─ [Edit] → User types new text → Agent 8 sends edited
    ├─ [Reject] → Discard + learn from rejection (Agent 9)
    └─ [Undo] → Agent 8 (trash sent email within window)
         ↓
  Agent 9 (Memory) — learn from every interaction
  Agent 10 (Mentor) — scheduled digests, reports, spam rescue
```

---

## Verification Plan

### Automated Testing (per phase)

| Phase | Test | Command |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | Supabase connection + table creation | `node scripts/setup.js` — verify all 10 tables created |
| 2 | Intake dedup test: send same messageId twice | `node test/intake.test.js` — second call returns silently |
| 2 | Filter classification: test with sample emails | `node test/filter.test.js` — verify bucket assignments |
| 3 | Context builder: mock email → verify context package shape | `node test/context.test.js` |
| 4 | AI Brain: mock Gemini response → verify JSON parsing + hard stop override | `node test/aiBrain.test.js` |
| 5 | Send pipeline: mock Gmail API → verify history recorded | `node test/send.test.js` |
| All | Health endpoint returns 200 | `curl http://localhost:3000/health` |

### Manual Verification (with user)

1. **OAuth flow:** Open browser → `/auth/google` → complete consent → verify tokens stored encrypted in Supabase
2. **End-to-end email test:** Send yourself a test email → verify it flows through all agents → appears as Telegram notification with draft and buttons
3. **Telegram buttons:** Tap Send → verify email sent via Gmail → verify appears in `email_history`
4. **Hard stop test:** Send email with "let's schedule a meeting" → verify Level 3 notification → must approve
5. **Undo test:** Send email via PA → tap Undo within window → verify trashed in Gmail
6. **Vault test:** Forward a receipt email → verify PDF stored in Supabase Storage → searchable via `/find`
7. **Morning digest:** Wait for 7am trigger or manually call → verify digest appears in Telegram

### User-Assisted Testing

> [!IMPORTANT]
> After each phase is built, I'll ask you to test the specific features by sending real emails and interacting via Telegram. This ensures everything works with your actual Gmail account and Telegram bot.

